                  , from her person
            </rs>.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-281-person2046">
                  MARY 
                  ANNE WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2046" type="surname" value="ANNE WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2046" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2046" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am <rs id="t18310908-281-viclabel1442" type="occupation">single</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-281-victim2045 t18310908-281-viclabel1442"></join>, and live at Enfield - I have been brought up with my aunt, and live with my friends till I get a place. I had been out with my friends on Saturday night, the 10th of July, and about half-past five o'clock in the morning I was near <placeName id="t18310908-281-crimeloc1443">Dalstonlane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-281-crimeloc1443" type="placeName" value="Dalstonlane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-281-crimeloc1443" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-281-off1440 t18310908-281-crimeloc1443"></join> - I had my reticule twisted round my fore finger, and felt the prisoner take it off my finger; I am quite sure he is the man - he was alone; he took it off without saying any thing - I immediately followed, and asked him several times to give it me; he would not answer, but walked on very fast - I kept him in sight till the officer took him, which was in three or four minutes; the officer heard me calling him to return it, and he took him - the reticule and contents were found on him; I never saw him before that.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Was it not thrown from the door where you were sitting? A. No, I was sitting at a door; he saw me, and came and took it off my finger - I had my head resting on my elbows, and the string of the reticule round my finger; I was alone - I had been with a few friends, and being very tired, sat down and fell asleep; the prisoner taking the reticule off my finger awoke me - I immediately got up, and went after him; it is not a place of resort for Policemen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-281-person2047">
                  THOMAS 
                  ROACH
               <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2047" type="surname" value="ROACH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2047" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2047" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I was on duty in Dalston-lane, about three hundred yards from where the prosecutrix was sitting, which was in a brickmaker's shed- she was a stranger to me; I saw the prisoner enter the shed, reach his hand forward, as if to take something, and steal back - I had not then see the prosecutrix; he entered the next field, and in about a minute the prosecutrix came round the field, and hallooed after him - I followed him to Hackney-downs, and took him; I found the purse in his right-hand jacket pocket, with a crown-piece, a half-crown, and 8s. 6d. in it - he said he had picked it up; I kept the purse concealed till I got to the prosecutrix - I then asked her the colour of it; she said red, which it was - he had the reticule in his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-281-person2048">
                  MARY 
                  ANNE WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2048" type="surname" value="ANNE WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2048" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-person2048" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My purse was in my reticule- this is it; this purse is mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been out of employ about four months, and had nothing to eat; I thought I could go<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183109080127"></xptr>down to Lincolnshire - when I got to Delston I was tired, I went into the brick-field, and sat down till one o'clock; I then saw some person, whether it was the prosecutrix I do not know - I fell asleep till nearly three; when I awoke I saw this old sand-house, and thought I would go and lay there - I went, and saw the prosecutrix and another person, who I suspected was the Policeman; they were asleep - I turned to where I had been laying, then got up, and came to this place - I saw something black laying about a foot within the door; I picked it up, and found it was this bag with some biscuits in it - I was very hungry, and did not think of there being money in it; I went on, took a biscuit out to eat, and a halfpenny dropped out - I then felt, and found the purse.</p>
               <p>M. A. WILLIAMS. I had been out the Saturday night with my friends: it was late when I left them, and I sat down in this place, about four o'clock, and dozed - there was nobody there all the time I was; I am sure I did not drop my reticule; there were four biscuits in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-281-verdict1444" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-verdict1444" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-verdict1444" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30.</p>
               <p>Recommended to Mercy. - <rs id="t18310908-281-punish1445" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-281-punish1445" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-281-defend2044 t18310908-281-punish1445"></join>
               Confined Nine Months
            </rs>.</p>
